RELEVANCE_TO_PROJECT:
This domain provides essential critical counterweight to valorizations of self-reliance in the moral value of DIY project. It identifies cases where delegation is superior to self-sufficiency and where self-reliance becomes epistemically and morally problematic. The literature on division of cognitive labor directly challenges the assumption that doing things yourself is always valuable, showing how specialization and dependence can be epistemically virtuous.

