  RELEVANCE: This foundational text is essential for understanding the relational autonomy tradition that challenges individualistic assumptions. For DIY ethics, it raises the question of whether the value of doing things oneself stems from an individualistic ideal of self-sufficiency that relational theorists would reject. Alternatively, relational autonomy might support DIY activities as ways of developing autonomous capacities through engagement with others and the world.

