  RELEVANCE: Benson's emphasis on self-worth and normative competence suggests a connection between autonomy and the development of competencies through practice. DIY activities might be valuable because engaging in them oneself develops and maintains the sense of competence that Benson identifies as necessary for autonomy. Systematically delegating tasks to others might erode this sense of normative competence over time.

