  RELEVANCE: Directly addresses how delegation can preserve shared agency. When a principal delegates to an agent within a framework of interlocking intentions and shared policies, the outcome may still reflect the principal's agency (though distributed through the relationship). This bears on whether delegated accomplishments can carry the same moral weight as individually performed ones.

