  RELEVANCE: Addresses central debate about what makes cognition cognitive and whether location matters. Relevant to DIY questions because it identifies functional integration as key—if external processes play the right functional role, they constitute cognition regardless of location. This suggests tool use can extend the self rather than delegate to something external when functional integration is sufficient. However, what counts as "appropriate integration" remains contested.

